# Hugo Markdown & Mermaid Rendering Rules

- **Mermaid Flowcharts**: DO NOT use Hugo shortcodes (like `{{< mermaid >}}`) for Mermaid graphs. ALWAYS use standard Markdown code blocks with the `mermaid` language identifier (i.e., ` ```mermaid `). This ensures the flowcharts can be correctly previewed in standard Markdown editors (like Obsidian/Notion) and correctly rendered by the Hugo site via the custom render hook at `layouts/_default/_markup/render-codeblock-mermaid.html`.
